sql:
SELECT battery_model, capacity
FROM batteries
WHERE capacity > (SELECT AVG(capacity) FROM batteries);

external_knowledge:
- Cumulative performance is the sum of data values recorded during each test for a battery; 
- Average cumulative performance is calculated by averaging the cumulative performances of all batteries from the same manufacturer in the same test environment; 
- Total batteries tested refers to the count of unique battery IDs for each manufacturer in each test environment.

sql:
SELECT AVG(bt.test_temperature * tr.parameter_value) AS temperature_parameter_product_average
FROM battery_tests bt
INNER JOIN test_results tr ON bt.test_id = tr.test_id;
